tion, alongside discus thrower M\\u00e9lina Robert-Michon.\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1841, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florent_Manaudou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2926873712762954e-18, \"text\": \"Florent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florent_Manaudou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florent_Manaudou\"}, {\"begin\": 1742, \"end\": 1753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.662568254042248e-15, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1820, \"end\": 1840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e9lina_Robert-Michon\", \"score\": 0.9999999999458851, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"M\\u00e9lina Robert-Michon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e9lina_Robert-Michon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e9lina_Robert-Michon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic swimming champion\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"the flagbearer\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1773}, {\"ngram\": \"the host nation\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1793}, {\"ngram\": \"discus\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1811}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That came just months after Manaudou had risked the wrath of his compatriots by questioning their love of sport.\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1955, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Manaudou\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 1879}, {\"ngram\": \"the wrath\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 1900}, {\"ngram\": \"his compatriots\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1919}, {\"ngram\": \"their love\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1945}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 1954}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to